<Layout title="Policy" disableHero>
<div class="BG555" style="padding: 2rem;">

  <h2 style="text-align: center;">Privacy Policy for Parlier NJROTC</h2>
  <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 1, 2025</p>
  <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Location:</strong> 601 3rd St, Parlier, CA 93648</p>
  <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:njrotcparlier@gmail.com">njrotcparlier@gmail.com</a></p>

  <p style="text-align: center;">
    This Privacy Policy describes how PARLIER NJROTC ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses,
    and protects information obtained from students and parents/guardians through our website
    and program enrollment.
  </p>

  <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
  <p>We collect only the following information during the sign-up process:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Student ID (issued by Parlier Unified School District)</li>
    <li>Grade Level</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not collect names, home addresses, phone numbers, email addresses, personal
    contact information, or financial information through this sign-up form.
  </p>

  <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
  <p>The Student ID and Grade Level are used strictly for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Verifying student eligibility for the NJROTC program.</li>
    <li>Internal program administration and record-keeping.</li>
    <li>
      Aggregate reporting to Parlier Unified School District (e.g., number of participants per
      grade).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
  <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share information only:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>With Parlier Unified School District officials as required for educational program compliance.</li>
    <li>If required to do so by law or to comply with legal process.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4. Data Security</h3>
  <p>
    We implement reasonable security measures to protect against unauthorized access to or
    unauthorized alteration, disclosure, or destruction of data. However, no method of
    transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.
  </p>

  <h3>5. Student Privacy Rights (FERPA)</h3>
  <p>
    The Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) affords parents and students over
    18 years of age ("eligible students") certain rights with respect to education records.
    Because we only collect Student ID and Grade, these rights are limited to requesting
    access to or deletion of this information.
  </p>

  <h3>6. Contact Us</h3>
  <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
  <p>
    <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:njrotcparlier@gmail.com">njrotcparlier@gmail.com</a><br>
    <strong>Mail:</strong> 601 3rd St, Parlier, CA 93648
  </p>
</Layout>